---
/**
 * /magpie/guide — long-form, non-interactive tutorial.
 *
 * Scrollable print-friendly walkthrough for someone who just installed
 * Magpie and wants a coherent explanation of what it does + how to use
 * it. No live data; no state; no JS beyond anchor-smoothness.
 *
 * Sibling page /magpie/tour is the interactive version — step-by-step
 * clickable with keyboard controls.
 */

import BlockLayout from '../../layouts/BlockLayout.astro';

const sections = [
  { id: 'idea',       title: 'The big idea' },
  { id: 'install',    title: 'Install + permissions' },
  { id: 'first-push', title: 'Your first push' },
  { id: 'broadcast',  title: 'Broadcast to many' },
  { id: 'composer',   title: 'Composer deep-dive' },
  { id: 'reach',      title: 'Activity + Reach' },
  { id: 'wallets',    title: 'Wallets + IPFS' },
  { id: 'cli',        title: 'Scripting with the CLI' },
  { id: 'settings',   title: 'Preferences overview' },
  { id: 'next',       title: "What's next" },
];
---

<BlockLayout
  channelCode="FD"
  blockType="READ"
  title="Magpie · Guide"
  description="A coherent walk through Magpie — capture, broadcast, reach."
  pageTitle="Magpie Guide"
>
  <article class="mg-guide-root">
    <header class="mgg-head">
      <p class="mgg-kicker">Magpie · v0.10 guide</p>
      <h1 class="mgg-title">Capture once, broadcast everywhere.</h1>
      <p class="mgg-dek">
        Magpie sits in your menu bar. Everything you copy becomes a clipping
        you can push to PointCast — and from there, to Mastodon, Farcaster,
        Bluesky, Twitter, LinkedIn, bitchat's mesh, or mint on Zora or Objkt.
        One compose, many homes.
      </p>
      <nav class="mgg-toc">
        <ol>
          {sections.map((s) => (
            <li><a href={`#${s.id}`}>{s.title}</a></li>
          ))}
        </ol>
      </nav>
    </header>

    <section id="idea" class="mgg-section">
      <h2>The big idea</h2>
      <p>
        Most publishing tools assume you sit in their composer and start
        typing. Magpie inverts that. You're already in Safari, Spotify,
        Warpcast, Zora — <em>capture where you are</em>. Copy a Spotify
        link, a paragraph, a cast, an image. Magpie holds it.
      </p>
      <p>
        Then: right-click the clipping. Push it to PointCast as a block, or
        broadcast it to every destination you connected. Each destination
        speaks its own native shape — char limits, threading, embeds — and
        Magpie translates.
      </p>
      <figure class="mgg-callout">
        <blockquote>
          "The front door is agentic."
        </blockquote>
        <figcaption>PointCast is your canonical home. Everything else is reach.</figcaption>
      </figure>
    </section>

    <section id="install" class="mgg-section">
      <h2>Install + permissions</h2>
      <ol class="mgg-steps">
        <li>
          <span class="mgg-step-n">1</span>
          <div>
            <strong>Download.</strong>
            <a href="https://github.com/Good-Feels/magpie/releases/latest" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
              github.com/Good-Feels/magpie/releases
            </a>
             — grab the <code>.dmg</code> and drag <code>Magpie.app</code> to <code>/Applications</code>.
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="mgg-step-n">2</span>
          <div>
            <strong>Launch.</strong> Look for the clipboard icon in your
            menu bar. First launch prompts for clipboard access — grant it.
            Magpie needs to see what you copy to hold it.
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="mgg-step-n">3</span>
          <div>
            <strong>Turn on the peer node.</strong>
            <em>Preferences → PointCast → Serve local web UI</em>. This is
            what lets the hosted page at <a href="/magpie">pointcast.xyz/magpie</a>
            read your clipboard + publish. Nothing leaves your machine
            unless you tell it to.
          </div>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <section id="first-push" class="mgg-section">
      <h2>Your first push</h2>
      <p>
        Copy anything — a URL, a paragraph, an image. Click the magpie
        in your menu bar. You'll see it at the top of the list. URL clips
        auto-unfurl: title, dek, OG image, host.
      </p>
      <p>
        Right-click the clipping and hit <strong>Push to PointCast</strong>.
        That's it. It lands in your PointCast inbox as a <code>pc-ping-v1</code>
        envelope. If you set a title, Claude Code will expand it into a
        full block on the next tick.
      </p>
      <p class="mgg-tip">
        <strong>Tip:</strong> right-click also shows <em>Broadcast…</em>
        which opens the full composer. We'll get there.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="broadcast" class="mgg-section">
      <h2>Broadcast to many</h2>
      <p>
        Right-click → <strong>Broadcast…</strong> opens the composer. At
        the top you'll see the clipping: source app, host, unfurl preview.
        Below that, channel + block-type pickers, title, dek, body.
        Below that, the <strong>destination stack</strong> — every
        connected publisher with a live preview.
      </p>
      <p>
        Each destination shows the exact text that'll be sent, the
        character count vs. its limit, and any notes — "will thread into
        3 toots", "+ URL embed", "will be truncated (no threading)". The
        compose-and-send model is one shared draft, many native renders.
      </p>
      <p>
        Over the destination row sit <strong>presets</strong> —
        one-click bundles: <em>Social</em> (Mastodon + Bluesky + Twitter +
        Farcaster), <em>Web3</em> (Farcaster + bitchat + Zora + Objkt),
        <em>Long-form</em> (PointCast + LinkedIn + Mastodon), <em>Mesh</em>,
        <em>Visual</em>, <em>All ready</em>. Use keyboard <kbd>⌘1</kbd>–<kbd>⌘6</kbd>.
      </p>
      <p>
        Hit <strong>Publish to N</strong>. Magpie fans the draft out to
        every selected destination in parallel. Each row in the composer
        gets a green ✓ or red ✗ when it completes. If a destination has
        a permalink, the ✓ becomes a clickable <em>→</em>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="composer" class="mgg-section">
      <h2>Composer deep-dive</h2>

      <h3>Per-destination overrides</h3>
      <p>
        Some platforms need different copy. Click the chevron on any
        selected destination to open an override editor — populated with
        what the adapter would send by default. Type your platform-
        specific variant. Twitter gets a quip, LinkedIn gets the
        long version.
      </p>

      <h3>Image attachments</h3>
      <p>
        The composer accepts up to 4 images per broadcast. Click
        <strong>Attach Image</strong> or press <kbd>⌘⇧A</kbd>. Attached
        clips that are themselves images get pre-staged automatically.
      </p>
      <ul class="mgg-inline-list">
        <li><strong>Mastodon</strong> — multipart upload to <code>/api/v2/media</code>, up to 4 images</li>
        <li><strong>Bluesky</strong> — uploadBlob XRPC, 4 images as <code>app.bsky.embed.images</code></li>
        <li><strong>Farcaster</strong> — auto-staged to IPFS via Pinata (if you've configured it), attached as URL embeds</li>
        <li><strong>Twitter / LinkedIn</strong> — text-only today; media lands in v1.0</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Scheduling</h3>
      <p>
        The clock button next to Publish opens the scheduler. Three
        presets (<em>+1 HR</em>, <em>TOMORROW 9A</em>, <em>+1 WEEK</em>)
        or pick a datetime. Scheduled broadcasts persist across app
        restarts; PointCast entries also get pushed to
        <a href="/api/schedule"><code>pointcast.xyz/api/schedule</code></a>
        so they fire even when your laptop is asleep.
      </p>

      <h3>Drafts + retry queue</h3>
      <p>
        A publish that fails with a transient error (rate-limit, network
        blip, 5xx) auto-queues for retry. Visit
        <em>Preferences → Queue</em> to see pending entries, retry
        individually, or <strong>Retry All</strong>. Drafts persist to
        <code>~/Library/Application Support/Magpie/draft-queue.json</code>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="reach" class="mgg-section">
      <h2>Activity + Reach</h2>
      <p>
        <em>Preferences → Reach</em> gives you a glance: 30-day
        totals, 14-day histogram, per-publisher success-rate lanes, and
        a 7-day block-type split. "Did this week's LISTEN clips actually
        travel?"
      </p>
      <p>
        <em>Preferences → Activity</em> is the chronological feed. Each
        outcome is clickable — click-through opens a drill-down sheet
        with the full title, summary, permalink (copy + open), and raw
        error text for failures.
      </p>
      <p>
        The same data is readable from your browser at
        <a href="/magpie/activity">pointcast.xyz/magpie/activity</a>
        — it fetches <code>127.0.0.1:38473/summary</code> + <code>/activity</code>
        directly from your running app.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="wallets" class="mgg-section">
      <h2>Wallets + IPFS (optional)</h2>
      <p>
        Only needed if you want to mint. <em>Preferences → Wallets</em>
        supports Tezos (native ed25519 via CryptoKit) and Ethereum / EVM
        (skeleton until v1.0's secp256k1 wiring). Keys live in Keychain.
      </p>
      <p>
        <em>Preferences → IPFS</em> takes a Pinata JWT. Once set, local
        image attachments auto-stage for Farcaster embeds and (in v1.0)
        Zora + Objkt metadata uploads.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="cli" class="mgg-section">
      <h2>Scripting with the CLI</h2>
      <p>
        <code>magpie-cli</code> talks to your peer node over loopback.
        Use it from zsh, cron, a shortcut — wherever you'd rather type
        than click.
      </p>
      <pre class="mgg-code"><code>{`# see what's in your clipboard archive
magpie list

# find something
magpie search "spotify"

# push clip #42 to PointCast
magpie push 42

# broadcast clip #42 to three destinations
magpie broadcast 42 --to pointcast,mastodon,farcaster

# schedule for tomorrow 9 AM
magpie schedule 42 --to pointcast --at 2026-04-22T09:00:00Z

# weekly recap
magpie summary

# see pending retries
magpie drafts
magpie retry 7b3f21a0   # first 8 chars of pending ID works

# scheduled queue
magpie scheduled`}</code></pre>
    </section>

    <section id="settings" class="mgg-section">
      <h2>Preferences overview</h2>
      <p>Fifteen tabs. You don't need to configure most of them.</p>
      <div class="mgg-tabs-grid">
        <div><strong>General</strong> startup, updates, notifications, retention</div>
        <div><strong>Exclusions</strong> apps whose clipboard Magpie ignores</div>
        <div><strong>Shortcuts</strong> global hotkey for the popover</div>
        <div><strong>PointCast</strong> endpoint, peer-node toggle</div>
        <div><strong>Mastodon</strong> instance + access token</div>
        <div><strong>Farcaster</strong> Neynar API key + signer UUID</div>
        <div><strong>bitchat</strong> Nostr nsec + relay pool</div>
        <div><strong>Bluesky</strong> handle + app password</div>
        <div><strong>Twitter/X</strong> OAuth 2.0 PKCE</div>
        <div><strong>LinkedIn</strong> OAuth 2.0 + author URN</div>
        <div><strong>Wallets</strong> Tezos (live) + EVM (v1.0)</div>
        <div><strong>IPFS</strong> Pinata JWT + gateway</div>
        <div><strong>Queue</strong> retry queue + bulk retry</div>
        <div><strong>Reach</strong> cross-destination dashboard</div>
        <div><strong>Activity</strong> outcome feed</div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="next" class="mgg-section mgg-last">
      <h2>What's next</h2>
      <p>
        v1.0 closes the remaining wallet paths: secp256k1 activates
        bitchat + Zora; Tezos RPC activates Objkt. Cloud-side cron
        dispatch expands to non-pointcast destinations via encrypted
        credential forwarding. Hardware wallet bridges (Beacon,
        WalletConnect) land alongside.
      </p>
      <p>
        Until then: you have a local clipboard that broadcasts to
        eleven destinations, with per-destination previews, presets,
        scheduling, a retry queue, a reach dashboard, and a scriptable
        CLI. That's the wedge.
      </p>
      <p class="mgg-signoff">
        — Ship something. <a href="/magpie">Back to Magpie</a>.
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</BlockLayout>

<style>
  :root {
    --mg-paper: #EFE8D2;
    --mg-paper-tint: #E7DFC4;
    --mg-card: #FAF5E0;
    --mg-rule: #C8B98E;
    --mg-rule-soft: #E0D6B6;
    --mg-ink: #1E1C14;
    --mg-ink-soft: #5A544A;
    --mg-ink-mute: #8A8273;
    --mg-moss: #3E5940;
    --mg-clay: #AE6A38;
    --mg-bronze: #7E5A2A;
    --mg-display: Georgia, 'Iowan Old Style', serif;
    --mg-mono: ui-monospace, 'IBM Plex Mono', 'SF Mono', Menlo, monospace;
  }

  .mg-guide-root {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 32px 24px;
    font-family: -apple-system, system-ui, sans-serif;
    color: var(--mg-ink);
    background: var(--mg-paper);
    line-height: 1.65;
    scroll-behavior: smooth;
  }
  .mgg-head { margin-bottom: 48px; }
  .mgg-kicker {
    font-family: var(--mg-mono);
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.22em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--mg-clay);
    margin: 0 0 6px;
  }
  .mgg-title {
    font-family: var(--mg-display);
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 40px;
    line-height: 1.15;
    margin: 0 0 14px;
    color: var(--mg-ink);
  }
  .mgg-dek {
    font-family: var(--mg-display);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 18px;
    color: var(--mg-ink-soft);
    margin: 0 0 24px;
  }
  .mgg-toc {
    padding: 14px 18px;
    background: var(--mg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--mg-rule);
    border-radius: 3px;
  }
  .mgg-toc ol {
    columns: 2;
    column-gap: 24px;
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 20px;
  }
  .mgg-toc li { font-size: 14px; break-inside: avoid; padding: 2px 0; }
  .mgg-toc a { color: var(--mg-ink); text-decoration: none; }
  .mgg-toc a:hover { color: var(--mg-bronze); text-decoration: underline; }

  .mgg-section { margin-bottom: 40px; scroll-margin-top: 16px; }
  .mgg-section h2 {
    font-family: var(--mg-display);
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 28px;
    margin: 0 0 14px;
    color: var(--mg-moss);
    border-bottom: 1px dotted var(--mg-rule);
    padding-bottom: 6px;
  }
  .mgg-section h3 {
    font-family: var(--mg-display);
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 18px;
    margin: 24px 0 8px;
    color: var(--mg-ink);
  }
  .mgg-section p { margin: 0 0 12px; font-size: 15px; }
  .mgg-section a { color: var(--mg-bronze); text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 2px; }
  .mgg-section a:hover { color: var(--mg-clay); }
  .mgg-section code {
    font-family: var(--mg-mono);
    font-size: 12px;
    padding: 1px 5px;
    background: var(--mg-paper-tint);
    border: 1px solid var(--mg-rule);
    border-radius: 2px;
  }
  .mgg-section kbd {
    font-family: var(--mg-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    padding: 1px 5px;
    background: var(--mg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--mg-rule);
    border-bottom-width: 2px;
    border-radius: 3px;
  }

  .mgg-callout {
    margin: 18px 0;
    padding: 16px 18px;
    background: var(--mg-paper-tint);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--mg-clay);
  }
  .mgg-callout blockquote {
    font-family: var(--mg-display);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 20px;
    margin: 0 0 8px;
    color: var(--mg-ink);
  }
  .mgg-callout figcaption {
    font-family: var(--mg-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    color: var(--mg-ink-mute);
  }

  .mgg-steps { list-style: none; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
  .mgg-steps li {
    display: flex;
    gap: 12px;
    padding: 10px 0;
    border-bottom: 1px dotted var(--mg-rule-soft);
  }
  .mgg-steps li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .mgg-step-n {
    flex: 0 0 28px;
    height: 28px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--mg-clay);
    color: var(--mg-paper);
    font-family: var(--mg-mono);
    font-weight: 700;
    display: grid;
    place-items: center;
    font-size: 13px;
  }

  .mgg-tip {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--mg-ink-soft);
    padding: 10px 14px;
    background: rgba(62, 89, 64, 0.06);
    border-left: 2px solid var(--mg-moss);
    margin: 10px 0;
  }

  .mgg-inline-list { margin: 8px 0 12px 20px; font-size: 14px; }
  .mgg-inline-list li { padding: 3px 0; }

  .mgg-code {
    background: var(--mg-ink);
    color: #E7DFC4;
    font-family: var(--mg-mono);
    font-size: 12px;
    padding: 14px 16px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    overflow-x: auto;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
  .mgg-code code { background: transparent; border: none; padding: 0; color: inherit; }

  .mgg-tabs-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr));
    gap: 6px;
    margin: 12px 0;
    font-size: 13px;
  }
  .mgg-tabs-grid > div {
    padding: 8px 12px;
    background: var(--mg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--mg-rule-soft);
    border-radius: 2px;
  }
  .mgg-tabs-grid strong { color: var(--mg-clay); margin-right: 6px; }

  .mgg-last { padding-bottom: 24px; }
  .mgg-signoff {
    font-family: var(--mg-display);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 15px;
    margin-top: 24px;
    color: var(--mg-ink-soft);
  }

  @media print {
    .mg-guide-root { max-width: none; padding: 0; }
    .mgg-toc { break-after: page; }
    .mgg-section { break-inside: avoid; }
    .mgg-code { font-size: 10px; }
  }
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .mgg-title { font-size: 28px; }
    .mgg-toc ol { columns: 1; }
  }
</style>
